\frac{dx}{dy}=(x^{2}-x-12)(1+\tan^{2}{y})
\frac{dx}{x^{2}-x-12}=(1+\tan^{2}{y})\:dy
\frac{1}{7}\left[\int{\frac{dx}{x-4}}-\int\frac{dx}{x+3}\right]=\int\sec^{2}{y}\:dy \\ \therefore \frac{1}{7}\ln{\left|\frac{x-4}{x+3}\right|}=\tan{y}+c
